Arc  (  1412–31 ). Claiming to be guided by the voices of the saints, she persuaded the French dauphin to defy the occupying English forces and have himself crowned, and she led the French army that raised the siege of Orleans in  1429 . The following year she was captured by the Burgundians and sold to the English, and a year later she was burned at the stake for witchcraft at the age of 18 or 19. Her story has captured the imagination of many writers, and she is variously portrayed as a national and political hero, a model of apolitical straightforwardness and honesty, and a religious heroine. She was canonized in  1920 . More recent influences have included the American film actress  Joan Crawford  (  1908–77 , born  Lucille le Sueur ), the British actress  Joan Collins  (  b. 1933 ), the American comedienne  Joan Rivers  (  b. 1933 ), and the West Indian pop singer  Joan Armatrading  (  b. 1950 )."],"variants":[{"name":"John","meanings":["Greek: the Lord gave graciously; whom Jehovah gave; whom Jehovah bestowed."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Joan Huntingfield married Robert de Sewerby on 2 February 1332. They were the parents of at least 3 sons. She died after 1346, in Heydon, Essex, England, United Kingdom."},"et":{"–aft 1346":"–pärast 1346","1280–1334":"1280–1334","1328–1334":"1328–1334","1311–1365":"1311–1365","–1353":"–1353","–Male":"Surnud","–1346":"–1346","bef `1332   (2nd wife  2nd husband)":"2. veebruar 1332","1346":"1346","1334":"1334","1311":"1311","1365":"1365","1353":"1353","aft 1346":"pärast 1346","1280":"1280","1328":"1328","Yorkshire, England":"Yorkshire, England","Sewerby with Marton, Yorkshire, England":"Sewerby with Marton, Yorkshire, England","Heydon, Essex, England":"Heydon, Essex, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"–aft 1346":"–1346 jälkeen","1280–1334":"1280–1334","1328–1334":"1328–1334","1311–1365":"1311–1365","–1353":"–1353","–Male":"Kuollut","–1346":"–1346","bef `1332   (2nd wife  2nd husband)":"2. helmikuuta 1332","1346":"1346","1334":"1334","13